12/10/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- The US Chamber of Commerce is interested in doing more business in Turkey, announced the chamber's deputy chairman, Jim Robinson, on Sunday (12 October).
He said that there are important opportunities in Turkey, in terms of commerce and investment.
"We will request our member companies to be interested in business opportunities in Turkey more closely," Robinson said.
He spoke in favour of advancing economically to make the country even more attractive to investors.
(Anadolu Agency - 12/10/03)
